ness_Purpose_Justification__c}</td>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td class="title" bgcolor="#0070C0">Description</td>                    <td colspan="3">{!relatedTo.ASI_CRM_Description__c}</td>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td class="title" bgcolor="#0070C0">Relation to Competitive Bid of Tender:</td>                    <td colspan="3">{!relatedTo.ASI_CRM_Within_3_Month__c}</td>                </tr>                                </table>                                <h3>Value Confirmation</h3>                <table width="100%" border="1">                <tr>                    <td class="title" width="25%" bgcolor="#0070C0">Value Per Recipient Per Occasion:</td>                    <td width="25%" class="money">{!relatedTo.ASI_CRM_Value_Per_Recipient__c}</td>                    <td class="title" width="25%" bgcolor="#0070C0">Actual/Apparent Value:</td>                    <td width="25%">{!relatedTo.ASI_CRM_Actual_Apparent_Value__c}</td>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td class="title" bgcolor="#0070C0">Accum value of Hospitality/Trips trvelling together per recipient:</td>                    <td class="money">{!relatedTo.ASI_CRM_AccumValueHospiPerRecipient__c}</td>                    <td class="title" bgcolor="#0070C0">Accum value of Gifts/Trips not trvelling togethe per recipient:</td>                    <td class="money">{!relatedTo.ASI_CRM_AccumValueOfGiftsPerRecipient__c}</td>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td class="title" bgcolor="#0070C0">Accum Value Per Recipient:</td>                    <td class="money">{!relatedTo.ASI_CRM_Accum_Value_per_Recipient__c}</td>                    <td colspan="2"/>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td class="title" bgcolor="#0070C0">Nature:</td>                    <td colspan="3">{!relatedTo.ASI_CRM_Nature__c}</td>                </tr>                </table>                                <h3>Public Officals</h3>                <table width="100%" border="1">                                <tr>                    <td class="title" width="50%" colspan="2" bgcolor="#0070C0">Does the Public Official have authority to award future contracts to, approve licences and/or examine or regulate Pernod Ricard China?</td>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td width="50%">{!IF(relatedTO.ASI_CRM_Answer_2__c==true,'Yes','No')}</td>                    <td width="50%">{!relatedTo.ASI_CRM_Q2_IF_yes_provide_details__c}</td>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td class="title" bgcolor="#0070C0" colspan="2">Are you aware of any current, proposed or anticipated business between Pernod Ricard China and the Public Official or the organisation which he/she works for or represents?</td>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td>{!IF(relatedTO.ASI_CRM_Answer_1__c==true,'Yes','No')}</td>                    <td>{!relatedTo.ASI_CRM_Q1_IF_yes_provide_details__c}</td>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td class="title" bgcolor="#0070C0" colspan="2">Are you aware of any transaction, contract examination finding or other business activity involving Pernod Ricard China before the Public Official?</td>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td>{!IF(relatedTO.ASI_CRM_Answer_3__c==true,'Yes','No')}</td>                    <td>{!relatedTo.ASI_CRM_Q3_IF_yes_provide_details__c}</td>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td class="title" bgcolor="#0070C0" colspan="2">If offering trips, pls proivde further information according to policy:</td>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td>{!IF(relatedTo.ASI_CRM_If_trips_provide_more_info__c==null,'No','Yes')}</td>                    <td>{!relatedTo.ASI_CRM_If_trips_provide_more_info__c}</td>                </tr>            </table>            <h3>                Anti- Bribery Compliance Officer's approval is based on 3 preconditions: <br/>                1)Your application already obtained your line manager's approval;<br/>                2)It is within budget;<br/>                3)It is in line with T&amp;E policy and/or other applicable policies.            </h3>        </body></messaging:htmlEmailBody></messaging:emailTemplate>